    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nWe don't have a CI build that compiles Nvim to some sort of web target that can run fully in-browser. Besides expanding the deployment scenarios for Nvim, this also would help us shape the story for a VFS (virtual filesystem), which is useful for other purposes (such as remote-ssh).\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n- Document build steps for WASM via clang (LLVM, not Apple Clang!) and/or emscripten.\n- Add to `doc/support.txt`.\n- Add a build task that produces a `nvim` artifact (emscripten, WASM/webassembly) that can run fully in-browser. \n- Add this build to our CI matrix.\n\n## Reference\n\n- https://github.com/MuNeNICK/nvim-wasm\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19863#issuecomment-1694325623\n- https://github.com/rhysd/vim.wasm",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk \n\nThank you for your reply earlier on https://github.com/vscode-neovim/vscode-neovim/issues/2295.\nI am considering creating a PR related to this, but I have a few questions beforehand.\n\nIn this issue, Emscripten seems to be the assumed toolchain.\nHowever, the build I successfully produced uses wasi-sdk instead:\nhttps://github.com/MuNeNICK/nvim-wasm/tree/master\n\nWould you prefer that this be based on Emscripten instead?",
